Our goal is to improve patient care and services today and in the future.  Because you are one of the first in your organization to gather information from a patient, you play a vital role in reaching that goal!

 

Click each button below to learn more.

Why Collect REAL Data?

Gather Information

You are often one of the first persons patients will see and with whom they will talk. By collecting REAL data, you will help your health care organization understand its patient care and better serve the needs of its diverse patient population.

Why Collect REAL Data?

Your Challenge

Your challenge will be to record what patients report as their REAL choices.

 

Guessing a patient’s race and/or Hispanic or Latino origin after only looking at him or her will not yield a consistent, accurate or complete report. You must allow your patient to self-report. Complete data collection will provide your health care organization with the most useful information for examining patient care and services.

 

Remember: Always use compassion and warmth when facing this challenge, just as you would with all sensitive subjects.
